            <title>[SPR-2861] Allow to restrict the visibility of beans to a file</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2861</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;All the beans defined in any configuration file are visible from the whole project. t would be useful to be able to limit the visibility of a bean to only the file where it is defined. Something like &amp;lt;bean-local ... &amp;gt;. I have looked in the forum and jira and I couldn&apos;t find anything like this.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
